Source: Auckland
Author: SWAINSON
Vol / Page: 106
Edition:
Quote: The dust consisted of flaky gold, of a pale lemon colour, largely intermixed with auriferous quartz, the separation having been effected only by washing in the simplest manner. <i>Ibid.</i> 109 These parties also brought up from the same spot various other specimens; one parcel of which, consisting of large rich dust and flakes, and exceedingly auriferous quartz (perhaps as rich, gaudy specimens as have yet been seen), was sold by auction by the undersigned yesterday.
Notes: 1852 Dec 13 Gold Circular in 1853 Swainson Auckland 106

